suggestion 5

The company does not know why students are not opening the email. I believe there are several ways to make an attractive email when the email is sent to the students.
 
1. Use words that make the email important to them. Put double quotes and capitalize the words.

2. Use a funny or eye-catching title and think about the time (time zone) when the students receive the email. Those kinds of strategies should help improve the email opening rate.
